	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hi,
<br />
<br />I was playing Super Turrican yesterday (on an emulator, though I do own the original cart), and noticed that the music tempo remained pretty much the same when played on NTSC and PAL consoles.
<br />
<br />So obviously that game detects the console type and adjusts accordingly. Are there any other NES games which do that?
<br />
<br />-- M

		

		</td>
	</tr>
