	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Speculation as to why this might be uncommon:
<br />
<br />On the Xbox 360 and PLAYSTATION 3 consoles, a game's publisher can opt out of region coding, unlike on any Nintendo console. So shipping one binary that runs fine on PAL and NTSC consoles isn't as critical on the NES as on the newer systems.

		

		</td>
